Implementors

In script::dom::bindings::trace

script::dom::bindings::trace

Trait JSTraceable 

Source 
pub(crate) unsafe trait JSTraceable {
    // Required method
    unsafe fn trace(&self, trc: *mut JSTracer);
}
Expand description

A trait to allow tracing (only) DOM objects. Types that can be traced.

This trait is unsafe; if it is implemented incorrectly, the GC may end up collecting objects that are still reachable.

Required Methods§

Source

unsafe fn trace(&self, trc: *mut JSTracer)

Trace self.
